version_description: Easier to play with capo on 3rd, and i think it sounds better to be able to hit the F# note before the Em chord.

There are no tabs for this song. It is important for Ultimate Guitar to have lots of tabs at the use of users and it was disappointing to see that no one else had made a, "King of Love" tab. The goal from me, for this tab, is that others will be able to use it to better their Ultimate Guitar experience. (Also, the song CAN be played with no CAPO, but to add a twist, CAPO 1 could be useful.

Track 1 off the the album Worship and Believe. Not a single yet but is an excellent album opener. Marches along pretty quick. Steven Curtis Chapman tunes down a half step and capos 4, but this is written for standard tuning. Capo whatever fits vocal range. https://youtu.be/SQ3NFn9IXps.
